summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2006 CHRYSLER 300. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE VEHICLE EXPERIENCED A LOSS OF ELECTRICAL POWER AND THE CHECK ENGINE WARNING INDICATOR ILLUMINATED. AFTER THE FAILURE OCCURRED, IT TOOK A WEEK BEFORE THE VEHICLE BECAME OPERABLE. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO AN UNKNOWN DEALER, BUT COULD NOT BE DIAGNOSED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 197,296.
